{l s='The General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) gives people the right to have incorrect personal data changed, or to supplement their personal data.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='In the GDPR (article 16) this right is described as right to rectification.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='You are responsible for ensuring that the personal data you process is correct and update this information if necessary.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='If personal data is incorrect in view of the purposes for which you are processing them, you are obliged to take all reasonable measures to rectify or supplement that information.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='Also when someone points out that his details are not correct or incomplete.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='If you provided incorrect or incomplete personal information to third parties you must also provide the modified or supplemented data to these organizations.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='If a person asks for it, you are obligated to inform this person which organizations you have informed.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='Inform people about their right to rectification in the text block above.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='Make sure you inform them how they can contact you. ' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
{l s='The easiest way is linking to the contact form of your shop.' mod='tbgdpr'}<br>
